description.narrative: The Government of Sudan has improved capacity in bottleneck analysis to plan for better health and nutrition outcomes in eight states. The updated evidence and data on the situation of girls and boys in Sudan are available to support multisectoral governance under the Scaling Up Nutrition Movement (SUN) and for FMOH to define the roadmap for a multi-sector policy and plans responding to the transitional government's priorities. In addition, the government's allocation of domestic funding has improved, demonstrated by increased contributions to the cost of traditional vaccines, syringes and other devices to 35%, an increase of 7% from 2018. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
